<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="83" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="83">Culture characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="83">On PDA, cultures are initially white, exhibiting light grey after 2 weeks. The colonies are flat with irregular edge; texture uniform, producing concentric circles with sparse conidiomata irregularly distributed on the centre of the plate within 1 month at 25 °C in the dark.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
